The [Ahmadiyah](http://www.multibrand.biz/2011/02/whats-wrong-with-
ahmadiyah.html) followers in Indonesia have been experiencing a series of
prosecutions in the country. In 2008, the government issued a decree
recognizing their existence but disallowed the group from spreading their
teachings. Since then, the members have been attacked in public places by
thugs and religious fanatics. However, the culprits of the previous incidents
were never arrested by the police.

The latest incident took place about eight days ago, when a mob of more than
1,500 people attacked an Ahmadi congregation in Cikeusik Sub District. While
the elderlies, women and children were able to flee the congregation house,
the Ahmadi men were attacked by a mob screaming “God is great”. The mob used
stones and machetes. Three of of the Ahmadis died, while few others were badly
injured, reports said that the victims’ bodies were later on hanged on trees.

A group of Human Rights NGOs including Kontras managed to obtain a lengthy
video recording of the incident. Some parts of the video were uploaded on
Youtube. The NGOs also claimed that the police didn't perform their duty by
allowing the attack to continue despite their presence in the area

The Banten Chief police was [stripped off his
rank](http://www.google.co.ma/url?q=http://www.thejakartaglobe.com/home/banten-
police-chief-loses-post-in-wake-of-religious-
violence/422150&sa=X&ei=VGpZTbzYKIO1hAeznfjjDA&ved=0CCwQ-
AsoADAB&usg=AFQjCNHoN_bu3-DgwocbTo4ZpeQ2DT3t4w) following the incident.

