Marjuki Alie on his _Politikana_ blog
[post](http://politikana.com/baca/2011/02/08/pembunuh-ahmadiyah-tidak-
bersalah.html) said that the Ahmadi murderers are not the ones to blame.

> […]hukum di Indonesia payah, mudah dibeli, mudah juga ditekan-tekan oleh
> kelompok-kelompok kepentingan.  
>  […]Kok pembunuh tidak bersalah, dimana logikanya? Mereka yang mengeroyok
> dan membunuh rame-rame itu pikirannya sudah sesat. Sesat gimana? Ya sesat
> karena mereka itu telah diajarkan bahwa yang mereka lalukan itu adalah
> benar. Mereka itu telah diajarkan bahwa yang mereka lakukan itu mulia, atas
> nama agama untuk membela agama.

Indonesian laws are weak, easy to be bought, easy to be pressurized by parties
who are protecting their interests. […] How come the murderers are innocent,
where's the logic in that? Those who gang up against the victims and those who
committed murder have lost their minds. How did they lose their minds? They
were taught that what they're doing is righteous. They were taught that what
they do is for religious sake and to defend that religion is noble.

